      5. Launch Template (VERY IMPORTANT)
      Defines how EC2 instances should be created:
        ◦ AMI 
        ◦ Instance type 
        ◦ Security group 
        ◦ Startup script (user_data)
          6. Target Group
          What it does
          Acts as a bridge between ALB and EC2
          Sends traffic to instances on port 8080
          7. Load Balancer (ALB)
          8. Listener
          What it does
            ▪ Listens on port 80
            ▪ Forwards traffic to target group 
              9. Auto Scaling Group (CORE)
              What it does
Setting	Meaning
min_size = 2	Minimum instances
max_size = 5	Maximum instances
desired = 2	Initial count
              Uses Launch Template to create instances
              10. Scaling Policies
              Scale OUT
              Adds 1 instance
              
              Scale IN
               Removes 1 instance
              
              11. CloudWatch Alarms
              High CPU
              If CPU > 70% → Scale OUT
               Low CPU
              If CPU < 20% → Scale IN
################# main.tf and variables.tf Explanation ######################
    • They are automatically connected by Terraform.
    • Terraform reads ALL .tf files in the same folder together.
    • Terraform internally combines them like:
    • (main.tf + variables.tf) = ONE configuration.
          How they connect?
In variables.tf:
var.instance_type → refers to variable defined in variables.tf
variable "instance_type" {
  default = "t3.micro"
}
In main.tf:
var.instance_type → refers to variable defined in variables.tf
What is variables.tf?
It is used to define input variables
Think like:
variables.tf = configuration inputs
main.tf      = actual infrastructure
How variables are USED in main.tf?
Example:
instance_type → var.instance_type
Terraform replaces:
var.instance_type → "t3.micro"
How Terraform reads it (Flow)?
When you run:
Terraform does:
    1. Reads main.tf
    2. Reads variables.tf
    3. Replaces all var.* values 
    4. Executes infrastructure
       What is terraform.tfvars?
    • It is used to override default values from variables.tf
    • Instead of default values, companies use:
    • terraform.tfvars
    • Environment-specific configs
Example:
variables.tf  → default values
terraform.tfvars → override values
main.tf → uses final values
